verbose_text: The dual-luciferase reporter assay system revealed that the relative luciferase activity of the wild-type + miR-421-5p group was significantly reduced compared with the wild-type + miRNA internal reference group, suggesting that miR-421-5p directly interacted with the MAPK7 3 '-UTR and inhibited the activity of fluorescein.
evidence: miR-421-5p directly interacted with the MAPK7 3'-UTR and inhibited the activity of fluorescein
